I go hang out at PC Bangs (cafes) once or twice a week.  3 months ago someone stabbed someone else with a knife because a CS game got too intense.  We will never know whether the insults, the game, or just the mood that guy was in that day was the cause.<br>
<br>
One thing for sure, and like other people already pointed out, the government sure jumps to the conclusion and point fingers/find a scapegoat to try to offset what negative feelings familys and friends of the victims may have.<br>
<br>
Correlation isn't causation.  Association /=/ Causation.  The people in charge certainly is not demonstrating that they are aware of this.  The title of this flame would be more suitable had it been &quot;/flame Governments that Jump to Conclusions Merely for Appeasement&quot;, perhaps.<br>
